<dl id="n12020g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12020g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12020g"> 20(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> SG. v S Michael</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Quand &eacute;clata la guerre pour la succession du duch&eacute; de Bretagne, Du Guesclin prit parti pour Charles de Blois, qui rendait hommage au roi de France, contre Simon de Montfort, qui reconnaissait le roi d&apos;Angleterre. <br><font color="green">[When the war broke out for the succession of the duchy of Brittany, Du Guesclin took the side of Charles de Blois, who gave hommage to the King of France, against Simon de Montfort, who recognised the king of England.]</font> <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 177</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: During the Hundred Years War, the English (Saint George) attacked Mont-Saint-Michel several times. </mm> </dd></dl>
